            <p>Atlanta G&#91;eorgi&#93;a<lb/>
                June 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1885<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. <sic>Morias</sic><lb/>
                Phila Pa<lb/></p>
                
            <p>My Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Information of<lb/> vital importance&#44; to me&#44; prompts<lb/> me to address you in asking<lb/> your kind advice re<lb/></p>
            <p>A Lady &#40;Gentile&#41;<lb/> living in this City wishes to become<lb/> one of our faith&#44; and the question<lb/> now arises what course to<lb/> pursue<lb/></p>
            <p>I am desirous<lb/> that only the Orthodox form<lb/> of Confirmation be used.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Please give me<lb/> some idea how to proceed&#44;<lb/> is there a printed form<lb/> of Obligation which I could<lb/> obtain&#44; or are there any<lb/> Books for sale or obtainable<lb/> giving the required instructions<lb/> to be learned by the Confirmant&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind attention<lb/> in this matter will place<lb/> me under lasting obligations<lb/> and of course I expect to<lb/> defray all expence &#38;c<lb/></p>
            <p>Trusting to hear<lb/> from you at your <sic>conveni&#45;<lb/>ance</sic><lb/>
                With best wishes<lb/> I am respectfully<lb/>
                Yours &#38;c<lb/>
                L.A. Ulman<lb/>
                25 Garnett St<lb/></p>
                
            <p><hi rend="underline">NB</hi>&#91;&#63;&#93; <hi rend="underline">Once</hi> S<hi rend="underline">ex</hi>ton of <hi rend="underline">Beth</hi> <hi rend="underline">El</hi> Emith Congregation<lb/></p>
        </body>
